From: HNSecW <fahongzhang99@gmail.com>
Date: 2026-05-02
Subject: [PATCH] arith: clear m_vC on Reset()

ArithSharing<T>::Reset() deletes the underlying buffers for every
Beaver-triple component except m_vC (the multiplicative C share).
That asymmetry was originally introduced because m_vC is partially
populated during OT and finalized in ComputeMTsFromOTs(); the legacy
implementation kept the previous-setup buffer alive so the OT output
mask could be xor-merged in place.  Subsequent refactors moved that
merge into FinishMTGeneration() but left the missing delCBitVector
behind, so on a Reset+reuse path the next setup phase re-Creates
m_vC[0] over a buffer that already holds the previous round's C
values.  Verifying with -DVERIFY_ARITH_MT confirms triples become
inconsistent (a*b != c) starting at the index where the second setup
re-enters the buffer.

The fix is one line: include m_vC[i].delCBitVector() in the same
delCBitVector loop that already covers m_vA, m_vB, m_vS, m_vD_snd,
m_vE_snd, m_vD_rcv, m_vE_rcv, m_vResA, m_vResB.

This patch is not strictly required when the caller deletes and
recreates the ABYParty between iterations (which is what HNSecW's
single_b2y.cpp does, since the Reset path also has independent OT
issues at high iteration counts), but applying it makes Reset()
self-consistent and removes a dormant buffer-reuse bug that would
otherwise resurface for any future caller that relies on Reset.

---
 src/abycore/sharing/arithsharing.cpp | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/src/abycore/sharing/arithsharing.cpp b/src/abycore/sharing/arithsharing.cpp
--- a/src/abycore/sharing/arithsharing.cpp
+++ b/src/abycore/sharing/arithsharing.cpp
@@ -1158,6 +1158,7 @@ void ArithSharing<T>::Reset() {
 	for (uint32_t i = 0; i < m_vA.size(); i++) {
 		m_vA[i].delCBitVector();
 		m_vB[i].delCBitVector();
+		m_vC[i].delCBitVector();
 		m_vS[i].delCBitVector();
 		m_vD_snd[i].delCBitVector();
 		m_vE_snd[i].delCBitVector();
